sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible ampicillin resistance cassette (regulated by LuxR + N-3-oxohexanyol-HSL)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The promoter for this beta-lactonase is induced by N-(3-oxohexanoyl)-homoserine lactone. Therefore the expression of the ampicillin beta-lactonase is inducable by Lux inducer N-(3-oxohexanoyl)-homoserine lactone.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is a combination of BBa_K1073002 and BBa_K1073000, which themselves were constructed from biobricks of the 2013 distribution kit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1073002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Inducible promoter of the lux quorum sensing system with RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is derived from BBa_R0062 and BBa_B0032. It combines the lux induced promoter with an RBS and can be used to clone it in front of a desired gene of interest, which shall be induced by lux.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The construct was combined from BBa_R0062 and BBa_B0032, which were taken from the 2013 distribution kit.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: ampR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence codes for a beta-lactamase, which degrades ampicillin. There is no RBS or other information attached, only the sequence for the enzyme plus prefix and suffix.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: iGEM Team Braunschweig 2013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The part was derived from BBa_P1002 ampicillin resistance cassette. The sequence for the beta-lactamase was gained by PCR of the original BBa_P1002 with appropiate primers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The primer sequences can be found on iGEM Team Braunschweig's wiki.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lux pR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter activated by LuxR in concert with HSL

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the LuxR activator protein complexed with the autoinducer, 3-oxo-hexanoyl-HSL. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules of the signalling compound homoserine lactone (HSL). This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This promoter is based on the Vibrio fischeri quorum sensing gene promoters. Two genes LuxI and LuxR and transcribed in opposite directions as shown below. The original sequence from which the parts BBa_R0062 and BBa_R0063 were derived is shown in the picture below.
